=== TEST 1: ngx.req.read_body() should work for HTTP2 GET requests that doesn't carry the content-length header
--- config
    location = /test {
        content_by_lua_block {
            local ok, err = pcall(ngx.req.read_body)
            ngx.say(ok, " err: ", err)
        }
    }
--- http2
--- request
GET /test
hello, world
--- more_headers
Content-Length:
--- response_body
true err: nil
--- no_error_log
[error]
[alert]

